      • stamp

        public void stamp(Property stampedBy)
        Stamps this Payload with a Property, marking that that Property has "seen" this Payload.

        A Property may only stamp a Payload once; attempting to stamp the same Payload multiple times will do nothing past the initial stamping.

        Parameters:
        stampedBy - the Property stamping this event.

      • unstamp

        public void unstamp(Property stampedBy)

      • tryToStamp

        public boolean tryToStamp(Property stampedBy)
        Attempts to stamp this Payload with a Property if this Payload has not already been stamped by that Property, and returns false if the Payload has already been stamped.
        Parameters:
        stampedBy - the Property stamping this event.
        Returns:
        false if this Payload was already stamped by that Property, true if not

      • stampExists

        public boolean stampExists(Property stampedBy)
        Checks to see if this Payload has been stamped by a Property, marking that that Property has "seen" this Payload

        Parameters:
        stampedBy - the Property who's stamp is being searched for
        Returns:
        true if that Property's stamp is present.
